28:51.079 --> 28:54.582
Once all the diplomas 
were handed out, what happened?

28:54.582 --> 28:58.219
Well, the report tells us 
that a representative of the class

28:58.219 --> 29:01.589
read a statement 
expressing the students’ appreciation

29:01.589 --> 29:03.758
for the privilege of attending Gilead

29:03.758 --> 29:06.127
and assuring the Governing Body 
of their loyalty

29:06.127 --> 29:09.130
to Jehovah and his organization.

29:09.130 --> 29:12.033
We’re going to follow the same pattern today,

29:12.033 --> 29:14.936
and Brother Richard Chilton is going to read

29:14.936 --> 29:18.306
a class letter on behalf of the class.

29:24.679 --> 29:26.748
“To the Governing Body.

29:26.748 --> 29:29.050
“Dear Brothers:

29:29.050 --> 29:32.654
“Few things in life 
bring greater satisfaction

29:32.654 --> 29:37.358
“than meaningful discussions 
on spiritual topics with dear friends.

29:37.358 --> 29:39.360
“Over the last five months,

29:39.360 --> 29:41.696
“we have enjoyed the blessing

29:41.696 --> 29:45.900
“of being immersed 
in such discussions on a daily basis.

29:45.900 --> 29:49.537
“As we studied the Bible book by book,

29:49.537 --> 29:53.107
“the examples 
of faithful men and women of the past

29:53.107 --> 29:57.045
“came to life and touched 
our hearts in new ways.

29:57.045 --> 30:01.049
“Reliving the modern-day history 
of Jehovah's organization,

30:01.049 --> 30:03.952
“we marveled at the faith,

30:03.952 --> 30:06.888
“courage, and self-sacrifice

30:06.888 --> 30:09.991
“of those who have gone before us.

30:09.991 --> 30:13.962
“Our skills in the ministry 
were refined through workshops,

30:13.962 --> 30:18.833
“and our desire to share 
in the preaching work intensified.

30:18.833 --> 30:20.969
“As the weeks passed,

30:20.969 --> 30:25.740
“fellow students became our close friends.

30:25.740 --> 30:29.544
“Now, as the class has come to an end,

30:29.544 --> 30:33.548
“tears come to our eyes 
as we think about parting ways,

30:33.548 --> 30:35.817
“but we will treasure the memories

30:35.817 --> 30:38.887
“of the stimulating 
‘interchange of encouragement’

30:38.887 --> 30:41.890
“with our new group of friends.

30:41.890 --> 30:46.427
“And what a blessing to be guided 
by mature, devoted instructors

30:46.427 --> 30:50.965
“who combined 
‘spiritual matters with spiritual words.’

30:50.965 --> 30:55.670
“We are grateful for their loving support 
as they nurtured our spiritual growth,

30:55.670 --> 31:00.675
“and we will never forget their example 
of zeal for God’s Word.

31:00.675 --> 31:05.013
“Getting to know the Bethel family 
has been a real delight

31:05.013 --> 31:08.249
“—young people 
who expend themselves energetically

31:08.249 --> 31:10.518
“in the service of the God they love

31:10.518 --> 31:13.254
“and older ones who display the wisdom

31:13.254 --> 31:15.456
“that comes with decades of experience

31:15.456 --> 31:17.825
“in applying Christian principles.

31:17.825 --> 31:20.528
“Their kindness, friendship,

31:20.528 --> 31:24.332
“and hospitality have touched our hearts.

31:24.332 --> 31:27.702
“Sometimes we think 
we know our friends well,

31:27.702 --> 31:30.438
“but our appreciation for them is enhanced

31:30.438 --> 31:34.876
“as we find out more about good deeds 
they have done in the past.

31:34.876 --> 31:39.881
“This has been the case 
in our relationship with our God.

31:39.881 --> 31:44.018
“Jehovah constantly surprises 
and delights us.

31:44.018 --> 31:47.255
“As we reflect on all that he is

31:47.255 --> 31:49.624
“and all that he has done,

31:49.624 --> 31:54.429
“we feel moved to praise his beautiful name.

31:54.429 --> 31:59.133
“While this school 
has far exceeded our expectations,

31:59.133 --> 32:02.770
“it has also left us longing for more.

32:02.770 --> 32:05.573
“We are resolved to continue our program

32:05.573 --> 32:08.209
“of meaningful personal study.

32:08.209 --> 32:12.580
“As Moses said at Deuteronomy 30:11:

32:12.580 --> 32:17.585
“‘This commandment . . . 
is not . . . beyond your reach.

32:17.585 --> 32:22.590
“It is not in the heavens, . . . 
nor . . . on the other side of the sea.’

32:22.590 --> 32:26.794
“In any situation, 
we know we will always find

32:26.794 --> 32:29.063
“an illuminating Scriptural principle,

32:29.063 --> 32:32.500
“an encouraging thought, 
or an informative article

32:32.500 --> 32:35.136
“to help us to do what is right.

32:35.136 --> 32:37.805
“Our Gilead course may be over,

32:37.805 --> 32:40.908
“but we are left 
with an even greater appreciation

32:40.908 --> 32:44.379
“for the wealth of spiritual food 
in our publications

32:44.379 --> 32:47.482
“which remains to be explored.

32:47.482 --> 32:52.487
“We would not exchange 
the past five months for anything!

32:52.487 --> 32:55.923
“We sincerely thank 
the Governing Body for arranging

32:55.923 --> 33:00.161
“for us to benefit 
from this magnificent spiritual education,

33:00.161 --> 33:03.965
“and we assure you 
that we will do all we can

33:03.965 --> 33:07.301
“to use these treasures to build up others.

33:07.301 --> 33:12.306
Your brothers and sisters, 
the 144th class of Gilead.”

33:39.867 --> 33:43.671
Well, what more can we add?

33:43.671 --> 33:46.674
All we can say is that we love you,

33:46.674 --> 33:49.777
and we pray Jehovah’s rich blessing upon you,

33:49.777 --> 33:52.980
and may this school of Gilead

33:52.980 --> 33:56.184
continue to serve as a symbol

33:56.184 --> 34:07.489
of the peace and unity 
of Jehovah’s organization.
